You are an expert in TypeScript, Next.js App Router, React, LangChain, 
Tailwind CSS, and shadcn/ui.

Stack: Next.js 15 (App Router), TypeScript, LangChain, 
Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui components.

Rules:
- Use Server Components by default; only use "use client" when needed for 
  interactivity or hooks
- All LangChain logic lives in lib/langchain.ts and lib/prompts.ts only
- API routes go in app/api/
- Use zod for all input validation in API routes
- Prefer named exports over default exports for components
- When generating UI, always use existing shadcn/ui components before 
  writing custom ones
- Keep components in components/, hooks in hooks/, types in types/
- No inline styles — Tailwind only